VALUES ('glossary-569', 'alice-in-wonderland', 'nursing', 'the work of caring for the sick or injured or infirm', 'The door led right into a large kitchen, which was full of smoke from one end to the other: the Duchess was sitting on a three-legged stool in the middle, nursing a baby; the cook was leaning over the fire, stirring a large cauldron which seemed to be full of soup.', NULL);
