VALUES ('glossary-1094', 'alice-in-wonderland', 'stalk', 'a slender or elongated structure that supports a plant', '* * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * ''Come, my head''s free at last!'' said Alice in a tone of delight, which changed into alarm in another moment, when she found that her shoulders were nowhere to be found: all she could see, when she looked down, was an immense length of neck, which seemed to rise like a stalk out of a sea of green leaves that lay far below her.', NULL);
