VALUES ('glossary-1809', 'alice-in-wonderland', 'terribly', 'in a terrible manner', '''Poor little thing!'' said Alice, in a coaxing tone, and she tried hard to whistle to it; but she was terribly frightened all the time at the thought that it might be hungry, in which case it would be very likely to eat her up in spite of all her coaxing.', NULL);
